rbot for Debian
---------------


Plugins requirements:
  (these are all optional, if you don't have them, the
  plugins just won't work)

  - slashdot: librexml-ruby
  - host: host
  - spell: aspell
  - cal: bsdmainutils
  - fortune: fortune-mod | fortune 

Plugins removed:
  - figlet: figlet is a non-free program

Plugins disabled:
  - urban: rubyful_soup dependency unavailable
  - tinyurl: shorturl dependency unavailable and silly dependency on rubygems


How to run the bot:
  Choose a directory to store your bot configuration (we are
  calling it <confdir>). Copy the configuration files example
  in '/usr/share/doc/rbot/rbotconf_example/' into <confdir>.
  Modify 'conf.rbot' to your desires and run the bot using :
    rbot <confdir> (<confdir> parameter can be omitted if
      the directory name is './rbotconf').
  

